race.comment: HALF SCOTCH (9) found a distant place behind a good one over 1400m at Warrnambool, and the provincial form leading into that reads extra well. Presents fourth up, and Yendall has been booked by the Danny O'Brien yard. Rates the one to beat. MY UNCLE DID IT (3) resumes for the Wilde yard, and she wasn't beaten far at her only fresh run. 1400m is a better starting point, and she's had three jumpouts. Hurdle is a positive jockey booking. SHADOW STORM (5) is third up, and expect more from her. Has a senior hoop aboard today and the speedy mare will jump and run from the inside gate. FOREVER JEUNE (1) is fit and tries hard. Has been giving away starts so the extra metres will suit. Should be around the mark.
